.SS tildr mv
Renames or moves a managed file inside the repository and updates its
symlink in \f[CR]$HOME\f[R].
Mirrors the behavior of the Linux \f[CR]mv\f[R] command \[em] rename and
move are the same operation.
.IP
.EX
tildr mv .bashrc .bashrc_backup
tildr mv files/file.txt configs/file.txt
tildr mv
.EE
.PP
\f[B]Options:\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]\-n\f[R], \f[B]\[en]dry\-run\f[R]
Show what would be done without making changes.
.TP
\f[B]\-q\f[R], \f[B]\[en]quiet\f[R]
Suppress output.
.PP
\f[B]Behavior:\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
Renames or moves the file inside the repository
.IP \[bu] 2
Removes the old symlink from \f[CR]$HOME\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
Creates a new symlink at the new path in \f[CR]$HOME\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
If the destination is a filename only (no directory), the original
directory is preserved
.IP \[bu] 2
If no arguments are passed, Tildr opens an interactive picker to select
the source, then prompts for the new path
.IP \[bu] 2
Auto\-commits the repository when \f[CR]git.auto_commit = true\f[R]
.SS tildr exclude
Manages patterns in \f[CR].tildrignore\f[R] without editing the file
manually.
.IP
.EX
tildr exclude add *.log
tildr exclude add cache/
tildr exclude remove *.log
tildr exclude list
.EE
.PP
\f[B]Subcommands:\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]add\f[R] \f[I]<PATTERN>\f[R]
Adds a gitignore\-style pattern to \f[CR].tildrignore\f[R].
Duplicate patterns are ignored.
.TP
\f[B]remove\f[R] \f[I]<PATTERN>\f[R]
Removes the exact pattern from \f[CR].tildrignore\f[R].
Fails if the pattern is not found.
.TP
\f[B]list\f[R]
Prints all non\-empty, non\-comment lines from \f[CR].tildrignore\f[R].
.PP
\f[B]Behavior:\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
Creates \f[CR].tildrignore\f[R] if it does not exist
.IP \[bu] 2
Patterns use gitignore\-style matching semantics
.IP \[bu] 2
Patterns added here prevent files from being discovered by
\f[CR]list\f[R], \f[CR]status\f[R], and \f[CR]apply\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
Does not remove existing symlinks \[em] use \f[CR]tildr unlink\f[R] for
that
