.IP \[bu] 2
Group operations work on files already managed by Tildr
.SS tildr secret
Manages encryption of sensitive files in your dotfiles repository using
GPG.
.IP
.EX
tildr secret add \[ti]/.ssh/id_rsa
tildr secret remove .ssh/id_rsa
tildr secret list
tildr secret encrypt
tildr secret decrypt
.EE
.PP
\f[B]Subcommands:\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]add\f[R] \f[I]<FILE>\f[R]
Registers a file as sensitive, adds it to \f[CR].gitignore\f[R], removes
it from Git tracking if already tracked, and re\-encrypts the full
bundle.
.TP
\f[B]remove\f[R] \f[I]<FILE>\f[R]
Unregisters a file from the manifest and re\-encrypts the bundle without
it.
If no files remain, the bundle is deleted.
The original file in \f[CR]$HOME\f[R] is not touched.
.TP
\f[B]list\f[R]
Lists all sensitive files currently registered in
\f[CR].tildr/encrypted\-items\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]encrypt\f[R]
Manually re\-encrypts all registered files into the bundle using their
current content from \f[CR]$HOME\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]decrypt\f[R]
Decrypts the bundle and restores all registered files to their original
locations in \f[CR]$HOME\f[R].
.PP
\f[B]Behavior:\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
GPG must be installed and available in \f[CR]PATH\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
Two encryption modes are supported, configured via
\f[CR][crypto].mode\f[R] in \f[CR]config.toml\f[R]:
.RS 2
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]symmetric\f[R] (default) \[em] passphrase only, no key pair
required
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]asymmetric\f[R] \[em] uses an existing GPG key pair;
\f[CR][crypto].gpg_key\f[R] sets the recipient
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
In asymmetric mode, if \f[CR]gpg_key\f[R] is not set, Tildr prompts
interactively and saves the chosen key to config
.IP \[bu] 2
The original sensitive files are never stored in plain text in the
repository
.IP \[bu] 2
Only the encrypted bundle \f[CR].tildr/encrypted.gpg\f[R] and the
plaintext manifest \f[CR].tildr/encrypted\-items\f[R] are committed
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]tildr sync\f[R] automatically re\-encrypts before pushing
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]tildr import\f[R] automatically decrypts after cloning if a bundle
is present
.IP \[bu] 2
Auto\-commits the repository when \f[CR]git.auto_commit = true\f[R]
.SS tildr sync
Synchronizes the repository with its configured Git remote in both
directions.
.IP
.EX
tildr sync
tildr sync \-\-dry\-run
tildr sync \-\-force
.EE
.PP
\f[B]Options:\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]\-n\f[R], \f[B]\[en]dry\-run\f[R]
Preview pull, merge, and push actions without executing.
.TP
\f[B]\-f\f[R], \f[B]\[en]force\f[R]
Pass \f[CR]\-\-force\f[R] to the final \f[CR]git push\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]\-q\f[R], \f[B]\[en]quiet\f[R]
Suppress output.
.PP
\f[B]Behavior:\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
Uses the current branch dynamically
.IP \[bu] 2
Uses the branch tracking remote and upstream branch from Git config
.IP \[bu] 2
Fetches from the tracked remote before deciding what to do
.IP \[bu] 2
If only local commits exist, pushes them
.IP \[bu] 2
If only remote commits exist, performs a fast\-forward pull
.IP \[bu] 2
If both local and remote commits exist, simulates a merge first
.IP \[bu] 2
Aborts safely and reports conflicting files when a merge conflict would
occur
.IP \[bu] 2
Uses the saved Git availability from Tildr config instead of probing
\f[CR]PATH\f[R] on every run
.SS tildr doctor
Runs a health check against the Tildr environment and reports any
issues.
.IP
.EX
tildr doctor
.EE
.PP
\f[B]Checks performed:\f[R]
.TP
Repository
Repository directory exists.
.TP
Config
Config file exists at expected path.
.TP
Git
Repository is a Git repo and the working tree has no pending or
untracked changes.
.TP
Permissions
Repository and managed files are accessible.
.TP
Disk
Repository total size on disk.
.TP
Symlinks
All managed symlinks are correct; reports broken or missing links.
.SS tildr completions
Generate shell completion scripts for various shells.
.IP
.EX
tildr completions bash
tildr completions zsh
tildr completions fish
.EE
.PP
\f[B]Argument:\f[R]
.PP
The shell to generate completions for: \f[CR]bash\f[R], \f[CR]zsh\f[R],
or \f[CR]fish\f[R].
.PP
\f[B]Installation:\f[R]
.PP
\f[B]Bash:\f[R]
.IP
.EX
tildr completions bash >> \[ti]/.bash_completion
.EE
.PP
\f[B]Zsh (Oh My Zsh):\f[R]
.IP
.EX
tildr completions zsh > \[ti]/.oh\-my\-zsh/completions/_tildr
.EE
.PP
\f[B]Zsh (vanilla):\f[R]
.PP
Add the following to \f[CR]\[ti]/.zshrc\f[R]:
.IP
.EX
fpath=(\[ti]/.zfunc $fpath)
autoload \-Uz compinit \f[B]&&\f[R] compinit
.EE
.PP
Then install completions:
.IP
.EX
tildr completions zsh > \[ti]/.zfunc/_tildr
.EE
.PP
Finally, restart your shell or run \f[CR]exec zsh\f[R] for changes to
take effect.
.PP
\f[B]Fish:\f[R]
.IP
.EX
tildr completions fish > \[ti]/.config/fish/completions/tildr.fish
.EE
.PP
\f[B]Behavior:\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
Generates and outputs shell\-specific completion scripts
.IP \[bu] 2
No interactive installation \[em] output is printed to stdout for you to
redirect or pipe
.IP \[bu] 2
Each shell has its own completion script format and installation
location
.SS tildr info
Displays project metadata.
.IP
.EX
tildr info credits
tildr info license
.EE
.PP
\f[B]Modes:\f[R]
.TP
\f[CR]credits\f[R]
Build metadata, repository URL, license, commit hash, maintainer,
homepage.
.TP
\f[CR]license\f[R]
Installed license text, opened through a pager when available.
.SH INTERACTIVE BEHAVIOR
When a target is omitted, the following commands open an interactive
file picker over the list of managed files:
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]add\f[R] (picks from \f[CR]$HOME\f[R] instead of the repository)
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]cat\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]edit\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]unlink\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]restore\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]del\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]mv\f[R]
.PP
When the number of managed files exceeds
\f[CR]core.search_threshold\f[R] (default: \f[CR]15\f[R]), the picker
shows a search step first.
Type a fragment to filter the list by fuzzy match, or press enter with
an empty input to skip filtering and see the full list.
.SH TYPICAL WORKFLOW
Initial setup:
.IP
.EX
tildr init
tildr add .bashrc
tildr add .config/nvim
tildr status
tildr apply
tildr sync
.EE
.PP
Recovery and maintenance:
.IP
.EX
tildr status
tildr doctor
tildr apply
tildr unlink .config/nvim
tildr restore .bashrc
.EE
.PP
Secret file management:
.IP
.EX
tildr secret add \[ti]/.ssh/id_rsa
tildr secret list
tildr secret encrypt
tildr sync
.EE
.SH OPERATIONAL NOTES
.IP \[bu] 2
Tildr is designed for home\-directory management on Linux and macOS
.IP \[bu] 2
The repository must stay inside \f[CR]$HOME\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
Relative paths for managed targets are interpreted from \f[CR]$HOME\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
Directory operations are recursive over all files under that path
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]apply\f[R] does not overwrite conflicting regular files unless
\f[CR]\-\-force\f[R] is provided
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]unlink\f[R] removes only symlinks, never repository content
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]restore\f[R] physically moves the real file back out of the
repository
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]del\f[R] removes repository content; use \f[CR]\-\-purge\f[R] for
permanent deletion
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]git.auto_commit\f[R] affects \f[CR]add\f[R], \f[CR]restore\f[R],
\f[CR]del\f[R], \f[CR]mv\f[R], and \f[CR]secret\f[R] \[em] not
\f[CR]apply\f[R], \f[CR]unlink\f[R], \f[CR]git\f[R], or \f[CR]sync\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]tildr secret\f[R] requires \f[CR]gpg\f[R] to be installed and
available in \f[CR]PATH\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
sensitive files registered with \f[CR]tildr secret add\f[R] are never
stored in plain text in the repository
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]core.color = false\f[R] in \f[CR]config.toml\f[R] disables all
colored output; the \f[CR]NO_COLOR\f[R] environment variable is also
respected
